body_html: We store all of our audio in a protobuf format that's roughly isomorphic to a WAV file (i.e. S16LE or float samples, uncompressed on disk). We use custom C++ ops to parse it / the associated metadata. tf.SequenceExample is pretty common, too.

body: We store all of our audio in a protobuf format that's roughly isomorphic to a WAV file (i.e. S16LE or float samples, uncompressed on disk). We use custom C++ ops to parse it / the associated metadata. `tf.SequenceExample` is pretty common, too.
